-- pitfalls --

invalid unit option silently returns 0. ms("1000ms", { unit: "minuts" })
returns 0 with no error. a typo in the unit parameter turns your duration
into zero, which can cause timeouts to fire immediately or intervals to
spin.

unrecognized units in input strings silently default to milliseconds.
"10xyz" parses as 10 (ms), not an error. a typo like "10m inutes" or a
malformed unit gives you a value orders of magnitude off from what you
intended.
